Monday, June 15th- Grades 6-8
Tuesday, June 16th- Grades 3-5
Wednesday, June 17th- Grades Pre-K-2

If you have school materials, and cannot make it on one of these days, please email us at info@alicecostello.com to arrange a drop-off time with school staff.

post_text:
This is a quick update regarding school closure:

Yesterday, in his daily briefing, Governor Phil Murphy stated that he would not revisit the decision to reopen schools until April 17th at the earliest. This means that school will be closed through spring break, and remote learning will continue for the foreseeable future. I will continue to update you on this matter, however Governor Murphy will not even be considering reopening schools until April 17th.

Have a happy Friday today everyone!

If you have questions, please reach out to your students’ individual teachers or email us at: info@alicecostello.com, and send us your remote learning pictures at community@alicecostello.com.

post_text: Thank you to Ms. Lee for bringing in a special visitor for the pre-k class as they study pets. Pre-K will be collecting donations for a local animal shelter throughout the month of February. Please feel free to send in donations for our donation box. Items include, but are not limited to: dog and cat food (wet and dry), paper towels, towels, blankets, cat litter, trash bags, treats, toys, laundry detergent, etc. Thank you!

post_text:
VACANCY - BROOKLAWN BOARD OF EDUCATION MEMBER

Requirements:

Must be a citizen and resident of Brooklawn 1 year immediately preceding appointment

Must be able to read and write

Must be registered to vote in Brooklawn

Must have no interest directly or indirectly in any contract with or claim against the Board

Must not be disqualified from membership for the conviction of certain crimes. (Within 30 days of election or appointment to the board, a member must undergo a criminal history background investigation through the state Department of Education.)

All interested parties please send a letter of interest to:

Mr. Sam Dutkin, Board of Education Secretary
301 Haakon Road
Brooklawn, NJ 08030
sdutkin@alicecostello.com

All letters of interest must be received by 3:00pm on January 8, 2020

post_text: Congratulations to Karelyne Morales Rivera and J.J. Meehan. Both students were not only chosen as Students of the Month, but also won the opportunity to be the "Superintendent for an hour". Karelyne wanted to have the "teachers be the students, and the students be the teachers" during her tenure. During J.J.'s hour, he "wanted the teachers to take a break." Great job, Karelyne and J.J.!
